            <title>[CASSANDRA-4475] Using &apos;key&apos; as primary key throws exception when using CQL2</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4475</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I run following CQL on trunk, throws exception (only in CQL2). This statement used to work and I think something is broken after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4179&quot; title=&quot;Add more general support for composites (to row key, column value)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4179&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4179&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;CREATE TABLE Standard1 (key ascii PRIMARY KEY, c0 ascii);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

